  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1664293836356-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1664293836356-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1664293836356-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1664293836356-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1664293836356-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>Fable pulled mushrooms </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1664293842989-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1664293842989-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1664293842989-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1664293842989-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1664293842989-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop your<strong> brown onion[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Peel and finely grate your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and cut into wedges</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>cannellini beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1664293846969-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1664293846969-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1664293846969-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1664293846969-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1664293846969-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reduce the heat to medium, then add the <strong>onion wedges</strong> and <strong>tomato paste </strong>to the dish with the <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>,<strong> ground coriander </strong>and <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Add 450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[750ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and the<strong> drained cannellini beans </strong>to the dish with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1664293850225-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1664293850225-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1664293850225-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1664293850225-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1664293850225-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, put the dish in the oven, uncovered, for 25-30 min or until the sauce has thickened – these are your <strong>Fable mushroom BBQ beans</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>remaining grated garlic</strong> with a<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>knob of<strong> butter alternative </strong>per person<strong> </strong>in a bowl with a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>garlic butter</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1664293853943-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1664293853943-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1664293853943-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1664293853943-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1664293853943-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1664293857131-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1664293857131-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1664293857131-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1664293857131-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1664293857131-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the Fable mushroom BBQ beans are almost ready, spread the <strong>garlic butter alternative </strong>all<strong> </strong>over the <strong>ciabatta halves</strong> (reserve the bowl!)</p><p>Add the <strong>buttered ciabatta halves</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, then put the tray[s] in the oven for 6-7 min or until golden and crisp – this is your <strong>garlic bread</strong></p><p>Combine your<strong> mayo </strong>and <strong>remaining white wine vinegar </strong>in the reserved bowl – this is your <strong>ranch dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1664293862585-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1664293862585-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1664293862585-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1664293862585-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1664293862585-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Shred the <strong>Fable mushrooms</strong> apart, using two forks and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>smoked sea salt flakes</strong> over the <strong>Fable mushroom BBQ beans </strong>and serve the <strong>lettuce</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>ranch dressing </strong>over the lettuce and Fable mushroom BBQ beans<strong> </strong>and<strong> </strong>serve the<strong> garlic bread</strong> to the side</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8,
